.git
.github
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
# TypeScript incremental build cache. Composite packages write a root-level
# `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo` (outside `dist/`, so the rules above miss it). If a dirty
# working tree's cache is COPYed into an image build, `tsc` treats declarations as
# up-to-date and silently skips `.d.ts` emit — leaving consumers with TS7016
# "Could not find a declaration file" (FUL-138). Keep image builds hermetic.
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo
coverage
**/.nyc_output
*.log
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
README.md
*.md
!apps/*/README.md
